  "body": "<!--\r\nNeed help?\r\nRefer to our contributing guidelines for additional information about making a good issue:\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/.github/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**\r\nWe would like to be able to be able to change the signing address of a contract account as well as delegate this power to a separate contract, e.g. a multisig for social recovery. \r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n1. Recovery address has the right to change the *signing address*, which is what signature verification is done against\r\n2. If the recovery address is non-zero it can also set itself \r\n3. If the recovery address is not set, the signing address can initialize what the recovery address is.",
